"649","<DOCUMENT>"
"650","<TYPE>EX-99.77B ACCT LTTR"
"651","<SEQUENCE>3"
"652","<FILENAME>4358auditletter.txt"
"653","<DESCRIPTION>ACCOUNTANTS REPORT ON INTERNAL CONTROL"
"654","<TEXT>"
"655","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm"
"656","To the Board of Trustees and Shareholders of Franklin Rising Dividends Fund"
"657","In planning and performing our audit of the financial statements of Franklin"
"658","Rising Dividends Fund (the Fund) as of and for the year ended"
"659","September 30, 2016, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company"
"660","Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered the Fund's internal"
"661","control over financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding"
"662","securities, as a basis for designing our auditing procedures for the purpose"
"663","of expressing our opinion on the financial statements and to comply with"
"664","the requirements of Form N-SAR, but not for the purpose of expressing"
"665","an opinion on the effectiveness of the Fund's internal control over"
"666","financial reporting. Accordingly, we do not express an opinion on"
"667","the effectiveness of the Fund's internal control over financial reporting."
"668","The management of the Fund is responsible for establishing and"
"669","maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting."
"670","In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates and judgments by"
"671","management are required to assess the expected benefits and"
"672","related costs of controls. A fund's internal control over financial"
"673","reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding"
"674","the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial"
"675","statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted"
"676","accounting principles. A fund's internal control over financial"
"677","reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1) pertain"
"678","to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately"
"679","and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets"
"680","of the fund; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are"
"681","recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements"
"682","in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and"
"683","that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being made only in"
"684","accordance with authorizations of management and trustees of the fund;"
"685","and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely"
"686","detection of unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition of a fund's"
"687","assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements."
"688","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial"
"689","reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections"
"690","of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to the"
"691","risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions,"
"692","or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures"
"693","may deteriorate."
"694","A deficiency in internal control over financial reporting exists when"
"695","the design or operation of a control does not allow management or employees,"
"696","in the normal course of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or"
"697","detect misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency,"
"698","or a combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial"
"699","reporting, such that there is a reasonable possibility that a material"
"700","misstatement of the Fund's annual or interim financial statements"
"701","will not be prevented or detected on a timely basis."
"702","Our consideration of the Fund's internal control over financial reporting"
"703","was for the limited purpose described in the first paragraph and would not"
"704","necessarily disclose all deficiencies in internal control over financial"
"705","reporting that might be material weaknesses under standards established"
"706","by the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). However,"
"707","we noted no deficiencies in the Fund's internal control over financial"
"708","reporting and their operation, including controls over safeguarding"
"709","securities, that we consider to be material weaknesses as defined above"
"710","as of September 30, 2016."
"711","This report is intended solely for the information and use of management"
"712","and the Board of Trustees of Franklin Rising Dividends Fund and the"
"713","Securities and Exchange Commission and is not intended to be and"
"714","should not be used by anyone other than these specified parties."
"715","/s/PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP"
"716","San Francisco, California"
"717","November 16, 2016"
"718","</TEXT>"
