"724","<DESCRIPTION>LEGAL ATTACHMENT"
"725","<TEXT>"
"726","NAME OF REGISTRANT"
"727","Franklin Managed Trust"
"728","File No. 811-04894"
"729","EXHIBIT ITEM No. 77q1(g): Exhibits"
"730","Agreement and Plan of Reorganization"
"731","THIS AGREEMENT AND PLAN OF REORGANIZATION  (the Plan)"
"732","is made as of this 29th day of April, 2016, by and between"
"733","Franklin Managed Trust (FMT), a statutory trust created"
"734","under the laws of the State of Delaware, with its"
"735","principal place of business at 55"
"736","Challenger Road, Ridgefield Park, NJ 07660, on behalf of"
"737","its series, Franklin Rising Dividends"
"738","Fund (the Acquiring Fund), and Franklin Value Investors"
"739","Trust (FVIT), a statutory trust created under the laws"
"740","of the State of Delaware, with its principal place of business at 55"
"741","Challenger Road, Ridgefield Park, NJ 07660, on behalf of its series,"
"742","Franklin Large Cap Value Fund (the Target Fund).  Franklin Advisory"
"743","Services, LLC (FAS),  a Delaware limited liability company,"
"744","investment manager to the Acquiring Fund and the Target Fund,"
"745","joins this Plan solely for purposes of Section 7."
"746","PLAN OF REORGANIZATION"
"747","The reorganization (hereinafter referred to as the Reorganization)"
"748","will consist of (i) the acquisition by FMT, on behalf of the Acquiring"
"749","Fund, of substantially all of the property, assets and goodwill of the"
"750","Target Fund in exchange solely for full and fractional Class A,"
"751","Class C, Class R, Class R6 and Advisor Class shares of beneficial"
"752","interest, with no par value, of the Acquiring Fund (the Acquiring
Fund Shares); (ii) the distribution of Acquiring Fund Shares to the"
"753","holders of Class A, Class C, Class R, Class R6 and Advisor Class"
"754","shares of beneficial interest, with no par value, of the Target Fund"
"755","(the Target Fund Shares), respectively, according to their respective"
"756","interests in the Target Fund in complete liquidation of the Target Fund;"
"757","and (iii) the dissolution of the Target Fund as soon as is practicable"
"758","after the closing (as described in Section 3, hereinafter called"
"759","the Closing), all upon and subject to the terms and conditions"
"760","of the Plan hereinafter set forth."
"761","AGREEMENT"
"762","In order to consummate the Reorganization and in consideration of the"
"763","premises and of the covenants and agreements hereinafter set forth,"
"764","the parties hereto, intending to be legally bound hereby, agree"
"765","as follows:"
"766","1. 	Sale and Transfer of Assets, Liquidation and Dissolution"
"767","of the Target Fund."
"768","(a) 	Subject to the terms and conditions of the Plan, and in"
"769","reliance on the representations and warranties herein contained,"
"770","and in consideration of the delivery by the Acquiring Fund of the"
"771","number of Acquiring Fund Shares hereinafter provided, FVIT, on"
"772","behalf of the Target Fund, agrees that, at the time of Closing,"
"773","it will convey, transfer and deliver to the Acquiring Fund all"
"774","of the Target Fund's then existing assets, including any interest"
"775","in pending or"
"776","future legal claims in connection with past or present portfolio"
"777","holdings, whether in form of class action claims, opt-out or other"
"778","direct litigation claims, or regulator or government-established"
"779","investor recovery fund claims, and any and all resulting recoveries,"
"780","free and clear of all liens, encumbrances, and claims whatsoever"
"781","(other than shareholders' rights of redemption), except for cash,"
"782","bank deposits, or cash equivalent securities in an estimated"
"783","amount necessary to: (i) pay"
"784","25% of the costs and expenses of carrying out the Reorganization"
"785","in accordance with Section 7"
"786","of the Plan, (including, but not limited to, fees of counsel and"
"787","accountants, and expenses of the Target Fund's  liquidation and"
"788","dissolution contemplated hereunder), which costs and expenses"
"789","shall be established on the Target Fund's  books as liability"
"790","reserves; (ii) discharge its unpaid liabilities on its books at"
"791","the Closing Date (as such term is defined in Section 3), including,"
"792","but not limited to, its income dividends and capital gains"
"793","distributions, if any, payable for the period prior to the Closing"
"794","Date and through the final taxable year ending with the Target Fund's"
"795","complete liquidation; and (iii) pay such contingent liabilities, if"
"796","any, as the officers of FVIT shall reasonably deem to exist against"
"797","the Target Fund at the Closing Date, for which contingent and other"
"798","appropriate liability reserves shall be established on the Target"
"799","Fund's  books (such assets hereinafter Net Assets).  FMT, on"
"800","behalf of the Acquiring Fund, shall not assume any liability of"
"801","the Target Fund, whether accrued or contingent, known or unknown,"
"802","and the Target Fund"
"803","shall use its reasonable best efforts to discharge all of its"
"804","known liabilities so far as may be possible, from the cash,"
"805","bank deposits and cash equivalent securities described above."
"806","(b) 	Subject to the terms and conditions of the Plan, and in"
"807","reliance on the representations and warranties herein contained,"
"808","and in consideration of such sale, conveyance, transfer, and"
"809","delivery, FMT, on behalf of the Acquiring Fund, agrees at the"
"810","Closing to deliver to FVIT, on behalf of the Target Fund, the"
"811","number of Acquiring Fund Shares, determined by dividing the net"
"812","asset value per share of each Class A, Class C, Class R, Class R6 and"
"813","Advisor Class shares of the Target Fund by the net asset value per"
"814","share each of Class A, Class C, Class R, Class R6 and Advisor Class"
"815","shares of the Acquiring Fund, respectively, and separately multiplying"
"816","the result thereof by the number of outstanding Class A, Class C,"
"817","Class R, Class R6 and Advisor Class shares, respectively, of the"
"818","Target Fund as of 1:00 p.m., Pacific time, on the Closing Date."
"819","The Acquiring Fund Shares delivered to FVIT, on behalf of the"
"820","Target Fund, at the Closing shall have an aggregate net asset value"
"821","equal to the value of the Target Fund's Net Assets, all determined as"
"822","provided in Section 2 of the Plan and as of the date and time"
"823","specified herein."
"824","(c) 	Immediately following the Closing, FVIT, on behalf of the Target"
"825","Fund, shall distribute the Acquiring Fund Shares received by FVIT, on"
"826","behalf of the Target Fund, pursuant to this Section 1 to the Target"
"827","Fund's  shareholders of record so that each shareholder receives full"
"828","and fractional Acquiring Fund Shares of the corresponding class of the"
"829","Acquiring Fund equal in value to the full and fractional shares of"
"830","the Target Fund held by the shareholder as of 1:00 p.m., Pacific time,"
"831","on the Closing Date.  Such distribution shall be accomplished by the"
"832","establishment of accounts on the share records of the Acquiring Fund"
"833","of the type and in the amounts due such shareholders based on their"
"834","respective holdings in the Target Fund as of 1:00 p.m., Pacific"
"835","time, on the Closing Date.  Fractional Acquiring Fund Shares shall be"
"836","carried to the third decimal place.  As promptly as practicable"
"837","after the Closing, each holder of any outstanding certificate or"
"838","certificates representing Target Fund Shares shall be entitled to"
"839","surrender the same to the transfer agent for the Acquiring Fund in"
"840","exchange for the number of Acquiring Fund Shares of the same class"
"841","into which the Target Fund Shares theretofore represented by the"
"842","certificate or certificates so surrendered shall have been converted."
"843","Until so surrendered, each outstanding certificate, if any, which,"
"844","prior to the Closing, represented Target Fund Shares shall be deemed"
"845","for all Acquiring Fund purposes to evidence ownership of the number of"
"846","Acquiring Fund Shares into which the Target Fund Shares (which prior"
"847","to the Closing were represented thereby) have been converted."
"848","Certificates for the Acquiring Fund Shares shall not be issued."
"849","After the distribution, the Target Fund shall be dissolved."
"850","(d) 	At the Closing, each shareholder of record of the Target Fund as"
"851","of the record date (the Distribution Record Date) with respect to any"
"852","unpaid dividends and other distributions that were declared prior to the"
"853","Closing, including any dividend or distribution declared pursuant to"
"854","Section 6(d) hereof, shall have the right to receive such unpaid"
"855","dividends and distributions with respect to the shares of the Target"
"856","Fund that such person had on such Distribution Record Date."
"857","(e)       All books and records relating to the Target Fund, including"
"858","all books and records required to be maintained under the Investment"
"859","Company Act of 1940 (the 1940 Act), and the rules and regulations"
"860","thereunder, shall be available to the Acquiring Fund from and after"
"861","the date of the Plan, and shall be turned over to the Acquiring Fund"
"862","on or prior to the Closing."
"863","2. 	Valuation."
"864","(a) 	The net asset value per share of the Acquiring Fund Shares and"
"865","the Target Fund Shares and the value of the Target Fund's  Net Assets"
"866","to be acquired by the Acquiring Fund hereunder shall in each case be"
"867","computed as of 1:00 p.m., Pacific time, on the Closing Date, unless"
"868","on such date: (i) the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) is not open"
"869","for unrestricted trading; or (ii) the reporting of trading on the"
"870","NYSE or other relevant market is disrupted; or"
"871","(iii) any other extraordinary financial event or market condition"
"872","occurs (each of the events described in (i), (ii) or (iii) are"
"873","referred to as a Market Disruption).   The net asset value per"
"874","share of the Acquiring Fund Shares and the Target Fund Shares and"
"875","the value of the Target Fund's Net Assets shall be computed in"
"876","accordance with the valuation procedures set forth in the most"
"877","recent respective prospectus of the Acquiring Fund and the Target"
"878","Fund, as amended or supplemented."
"879","(b) 	In the event of a Market Disruption on the proposed Closing"
"880","Date so that an accurate appraisal of the net asset value per share"
"881","of the Acquiring Fund Shares or Target"
"882","Fund Shares or the value of the Target Fund's  Net Assets is"
"883","impracticable, the Closing Date shall be postponed until the"
"884","first business day when regular trading on the NYSE shall have"
"885","been fully resumed and reporting shall have been restored and"
"886","other trading markets are otherwise stabilized."
"887","(c)       All computations of value regarding the net asset value"
"888","per share of the Acquiring Fund Shares and Target Fund Shares and"
"889","the value of the Target Fund's Net Assets shall be made by the"
"890","administrator to the Acquiring Fund and Target Fund."
"891","3. 	Closing and Closing Date."
"892","The Closing shall take place at the principal office of FMT at"
"893","1:00 p.m., Pacific time, on May 20, 2016 or such later date as"
"894","the officers of FMT and FVIT may mutually agree (the Closing Date)."
"895","FVIT, on behalf of the Target Fund, shall have provided for"
"896","delivery as of the Closing those Net Assets to be transferred"
"897","to the account of the Acquiring Fund's custodian, The Bank of"
"898","New York Mellon, Mutual Funds Division, 100 Church Street,"
"899","New York, NY"
"900","10286.  FVIT, on behalf of the Target Fund, shall deliver at the"
"901","Closing a list of names and addresses of the holders of record of"
"902","each class of the Target Fund and the number of full and fractional"
"903","shares of beneficial interest owned by each such shareholder,"
"904","indicating thereon which such shares are represented by"
"905","outstanding certificates and which by book-entry accounts, as of"
"906","1:00 p.m., Pacific time, on the Closing Date.  FMT, on behalf of the"
"907","Acquiring Fund, shall provide evidence that such Acquiring Fund"
"908","Shares have been registered in an account on the books of Acquiring"
"909","Fund in such manner as the officers of FVIT may reasonably request."
"910","4. 	Representations and Warranties."
"911","4.1. 	FMT, on behalf of the Acquiring Fund, represents and"
"912","warrants that:"
"913","(a) 	The Acquiring Fund is a series of FMT, which was originally"
"914","organized as a Massachusetts business trust on July 15, 1986, and was"
"915","reorganized as a Delaware statutory trust effective on"
"916","October 26, 1999. FMT is validly existing under the laws of the"
"917","State of Delaware.  FMT is duly registered under the 1940 Act as"
"918","an open-end management investment company and the Acquiring Fund's"
"919","shares sold were sold pursuant to an effective registration statement"
"920","filed under the Securities Act of 1933 (the 1933 Act), except for"
"921","those shares sold pursuant to the private offering exemption for the"
"922","purpose of raising initial capital or obtaining any required initial"
"923","shareholder approvals."
"924","(b) 	FMT is authorized to issue an unlimited number of shares of"
"925","beneficial interest, without par value, of the Acquiring Fund."
"926","Each outstanding share of the Acquiring Fund is fully paid,"
"927","non-assessable, and has full voting rights, and each Acquiring"
"928","Fund Share when issued pursuant to and in accordance with the"
"929","Plan, will be fully paid, non-assessable, and will have full"
"930","voting rights.  The Acquiring Fund currently is divided into"
"931","five classes of shares: Class A, Class C, Class R, Class R6 and"
"932","Advisor Class shares of beneficial interest, which represent Acquiring"
"933","Fund Shares.  An unlimited number of shares of beneficial interest of"
"934","the Acquiring Fund has been allocated and designated to each class of"
"935","the Acquiring Fund."
"936","(c) 	FMT, on behalf of the Acquiring Fund, is not a party to or"
"937","obligated under any provision of its Agreement and Declaration of"
"938","Trust, as amended, or By-laws, as amended, or any contract or any"
"939","other commitment or obligation and is not subject to any order or"
"940","decree, that would be violated by its execution of or performance"
"941","under the Plan, and no consent,"
"942","approval, authorization or order of any court or governmental"
"943","authority is required for the consummation by FMT, on behalf of"
"944","the Acquiring Fund, of the transactions contemplated by the Plan,"
"945","except for the registration of Acquiring Fund Shares under the 1933"
"946","Act, the 1940 Act, or as may otherwise be required under the federal"
"947","and state securities laws or the rules and regulations thereunder."
"948","(d) 	The financial statements appearing in the Acquiring Fund's"
"949","Annual Report to Shareholders for the fiscal year ended"
"950","September 30, 2015, audited by Tait, Weller & Baker LLP, and"
"951","any interim unaudited financial statements, fairly present the"
"952","financial position of the Acquiring Fund as of their respective"
"953","dates and the results of the Acquiring Fund's operations for periods"
"954","indicated, in conformity with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles"
"955","applied on a consistent basis."
"956","(e) 	The books and records of the Acquiring Fund accurately summarize"
"957","the accounting data represented and contain no material omissions with"
"958","respect to the business and operations of the Acquiring Fund."
"959","(f) 	FMT has elected to treat the Acquiring Fund as a regulated"
"960","investment company (RIC) for federal income tax purposes under Part"
"961","I of Subchapter M of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended"
"962","(the Code).  The Acquiring Fund is a fund as defined in Section"
"963","851(g)(2) of the Code, has qualified as a RIC for each taxable year"
"964","since its inception, has not had any earnings and profits accumulated"
"965","in any taxable year to which the provisions of Subchapter M of the Code"
"966","(or the corresponding provisions of prior law) did not apply, and"
"967","intends to continue to qualify as a RIC after the Closing Date."
"968","Consummation of the transactions contemplated by the Plan will not"
"969","cause the Acquiring Fund to fail to be qualified as a RIC as of the"
"970","Closing Date."
"971","(g) 	The Acquiring Fund does not have any unamortized or unpaid"
"972","organizational fees or expenses."
"973","(h) 	The Acquiring Fund does not have any known liabilities,"
"974","costs or expenses of a material amount, contingent or otherwise,"
"975","other than those reflected in the financial statements referred to"
"976","in Section 4.l(d) hereof and those incurred in the ordinary course"
"977","of business as an investment company and of a nature and amount"
"978","similar to, and consistent with, those shown in such financial"
"979","statements since the dates of those financial statements."
"980","(i) 	There is no inter-corporate indebtedness existing between"
"981","the Target Fund and the Acquiring Fund that was issued, acquired,"
"982","or will be settled at a discount."
"983","G)	The registration statement on Form N-14 referred to in"
"984","Section 5.1(a) hereof (the Registration  Statement), including"
"985","any prospectus or statement of additional information contained"
"986","or incorporated therein by reference and any supplements or"
"987","amendments thereto, insofar as it relates to the Acquiring"
"988","Fund and the Acquiring Fund Shares, will, from the effective"
"989","date of the Registration Statement through the date of the"
"990","special meeting of the Target Fund's  shareholders"
"991","(the Special Meeting) and on the Closing Date:  (i)"
"992","comply, as amended, in all material respects with the"
"993","provisions of the 1933 Act, the Securities Exchange Act of 1934"
"994","(the 1934 Act), the 1940 Act, the rules and regulations"
"995","thereunder, and all applicable state"
"996","Securities laws and the rules and regulations thereunder;"
"997","and (ii) not contain any untrue statement"
"998","of a material fact or omit to state any material fact"
"999","required to be stated therein or necessary to make the"
"1000","statements therein, in light of the circumstances under"
"1001","which the statements were made, not misleading, provided,"
"1002","however, that the representations and warranties of this"
"1003","subparagraph shall not apply to statements in or omissions"
"1004","from the Registration Statement made in reliance upon and in"
"1005","conformity with information that was furnished by the Target"
"1006","Fund for use therein."
"1007","(k) 	Since September 30, 2015, there has not been any"
"1008","material adverse change in the Acquiring Fund's financial"
"1009","condition, assets, liabilities or business other than changes"
"1010","occurring in the ordinary course of business."
"1011","(1)	On the Closing Date, all material Returns"
"1012","(as defined below) of the"
"1013","Acquiring Fund required by law to have been filed by such date"
"1014","(including any extensions) shall"
"1015","have been filed and are or will be true, correct and"
"1016","complete in all material respects, and all"
"1017","Taxes (as defined below) shown as due or claimed to be"
"1018","due by any government entity shall have been paid or"
"1019","provision has been made for the payment thereof.  To"
"1020","FMT's knowledge, no such Return is currently under"
"1021","audit by any federal, state, local or foreign Tax"
"1022","authority; no"
"1023","assessment has been asserted with respect to such Returns;"
"1024","there are no levies, liens or other"
"1025","encumbrances on the Acquiring Fund or its assets resulting"
"1026","from the non-payment of any Taxes; no waivers of the time to"
"1027","assess any such Taxes are outstanding nor are any written"
"1028","requests for such waivers pending; and adequate provision has"
"1029","been made in the Acquiring Fund's financial statements for all"
"1030","Taxes in respect of all periods ended on or before the date of"
